";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:34:\"mc101-textless-thumb1-1038x576.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:1038;s:6:\"height\";i:576;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}}s:10:\"image_meta\";a:10:{s:8:\"aperture\";i:0;s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:0;s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";i:0;s:3:\"iso\";i:0;s:13:\"shutter_speed\";i:0;s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";}}'),(636,220,'_edit_lock','1411987696:1'),(637,220,'youtube_video_embed','a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:23:\"alternative-video-title\";s:50:\"Texan high schooler demands<br>real sex ed classes\";s:24:\"video-embed-code-or-link\";s:42:\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_BiMtsLMIzU\";s:15:\"video-thumbnail\";s:3:\"214\";s:10:\"video-text\";s:48:\"Click \"cc\" for subtitles in different languages.\";s:5:\"order\";s:0:\"\";}}'),(638,220,'_edit_last','1'),(639,107,'_post_restored_from','a:3:{s:20:\"restored_revision_id\";i:135;s:16:\"restored_by_user\";i:2;s:13:\"restored_time\";i:1410797596;}'),(640,109,'td-layout-1','a:1:{i:0;a:7:{s:20:\"left-first-paragraph\";s:0:\"\";s:21:\"left-second-paragraph\";s:0:\"\";s:20:\"left-third-paragraph\";s:0:\"\";s:15:\"right-paragraph\";s:0:\"\";s:10:\"mid-region\";s:2783:\"Concretely, how will this vision apply to the innovators at Human Condition Labs? We’re introducing them to a rigorous curriculum known as Moral Courage 101, 102 and 103. The first two of these courses will be required of every Lab employee and resident (those who come to the Labs to develop projects). The last course will be an elective, based on specific interests expressed by residents. Given the grand ambitions of our residents, and the risks that go with those ambitions, their moral courage will be tested throughout their time at HC Labs. At the same time, their capacity for success is deepened.\n<br><br>\nWe also have a menu of offerings to non-resident clients, be they other innovation hubs, companies, schools, government agencies, or individuals:\n<br><br>\n<b>Seminars</b>\n<br><br>\nIrshad and her team will teach you and your team the Applied Courage curriculum at HC Labs. It’s an immersive experience that, depending on your needs, can last 3 hours or 5 days. \n<br><br>\nWe’re currently designing an online course with original, multimedia content. But the Applied Courage experience doesn’t end there. Our seminars and modules emphasize engagement between real people. Students learn collaboratively, leveraging the emotional advantage of human interaction. Be prepared to show up in the Big Apple!\n<br><br>\n<b>Mentors</b>\n<br><br>\nMany of our students will eventually become Moral Courage Mentors. Organizations that take our training will have a Moral Courage Mentor assigned to them for quality control and on-going growth. For individuals who wish to coach their communities in Moral Courage, we also offer the opportunity to become certified and paid. \n<br><br>\nHC Labs is an ideal place from which to be training a worldwide cohort of Moral Courage Mentors: They’ll learn not only the philosophy and pedagogy of Applied Courage, but they’ll also be free to experiment with the curriculum in their respective cultures – institutional, national, ethnic and religious. \n<br><br>\n<b>Research</b>\n<br><br>\nAs part of HC Labs’ own public service, we’re creating a not-for-profit Moral Courage Academy that generates, collects and shares cutting-edge research on how to raise “gutsy global citizens.” By “gutsy,” we mean individuals who think and act outside of the standard points of view they’re surrounded by, and see human problems through fresh lenses. \n<br><br>\nThe Academy will also be a place for them to gather and exchange notes with our mentors, as well as with Irshad, so that the Applied Courage curriculum can evolve through the insights of doers. We’ll make all of our research accessible to teachers, scientists, chief learning officers, policymakers, parents and student leaders, broadening the moral courage community. \";s:19:\"bottom-region-title\";s:115:\"Are you ready to get gutsy together? <br><br> <a href=\"[base_url]/contact\" class=\"contact-btn\">Contact our team</a>\";s:13:\"bottom-region\";s:0:\"\";}}'),(641,109,'testimonial-list','a:0:{}'),(642,111,'td-layout-1','a:1:{i:0;a:7:{s:20:\"left-first-paragraph\";s:309:\"<b>Buddha</b> challenged the elitism of Hindu priests.\n<br><br>\n<b>Abraham</b> argued with God for the sake of justice.\n<br><br>\n<b>Jesus</b> spoke truth to Roman power.\n<br><br>\n<b>Mohammed</b> stopped female infanticide.\n<br><br>Our job is to replace the dogma of theologians with the faith of the prophets.\";s:21:\"left-second-paragraph\";s:0:\"\";s:20:\"left-third-paragraph\";s:0:\"\";s:15:\"right-paragraph\";s:449:\"Irshad Manji, founder of the Moral Courage Project, equips spiritual leaders to disrupt dogma and keep the faith.\n<br><br>She started her own journey as a Muslim with questions about scripture, culture, fear and love. Now one of the world\'s most renowned Muslim reformists, Irshad has translated her story into mentorship for leaders across the religious spectrum.\n<br><br><b>Call it your professional development, or just call it your calling.</b>\";s:10:\"mid-region\";s:83:\"<a href=\"[base_url]/contact\" class=\"contact-btn\">Contact the Moral Courage Team</a>\";s:19:\"bottom-region-title\";s:0:\"\";s:13:\"bottom-region\";s:0:\"\";}}'),(643,111,'testimonial-list','a:4:{i:0;a:2:{s:5:\"quote\";s:196:\"Irshad spoke on stage with His Holiness the Dalai Lama. He, in turn, picked up and reinforced her message - that questioning is a basic human need. That is how infectious Irshad\'s spirituality is.\";s:6:\"author\";s:23:\"Common Ground for Peace\";}i:1;a:2:{s:5:\"quote\";s:227:\"The Moral Courage Project is a hands-on partner in our commitment to put faith into action. In Irshad, we have an invaluable soulmate who motivates the young across faith traditions, adding immeasurably to our own congregation.\";s:6:\"author\";s:24:\"Middle Collegiate Church\";}i:2;a:2:{s:5:\"quote\";s:27:\"Moral Courage is my mosque.\";s:6:\"author\";s:12:\"Facebook fan\";}i:3;a:2:{s:5:\"quote\";s:129:\"The space that @MoralCourage creates 4 youth 2 ask questions, engage our spiritual leaders & think for ourselves is long overdue.\";s:6:\"author\";s:16:\"Twitter follower\";}}'),(644,224,'_wp_attached_file','2014/08/Itmum-for-website.jpg'),(645,224,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:5:{s:5:\"width\";i:3648;s:6:\"height\";i:2736;s:4:\"file\";s:29:\"2014/08/Itmum-for-website.jpg\";s:5:\"sizes\";a:5:{s:9:\"thumbnail\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:29:\"Itmum-for-website-150x150.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:150;s:6:\"height\";i:150;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:6:\"medium\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:29:\"Itmum-for-website-300x225.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:300;s:6:\"height\";i:225;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:5:\"large\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:30:\"Itmum-for-website-1024x768.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:1024;s:6:\"height\";i:768;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:14:\"post-thumbnail\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:29:\"Itmum-for-website-672x372.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:672;s:6:\"height\";i:372;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}s:25:\"twentyfourteen-full-width\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:30:\"Itmum-for-website-1038x576.jpg\";s:5:\"width\";i:1038;s:6:\"height\";i:576;s:9:\"mime-type\";s:10:\"image/jpeg\";}}s:10:\"image_meta\";a:10:{s:8:\"aperture\";d:3.2000000000000002;s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:19:\"Canon PowerShot G12\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";i:1409405983;s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";s:5:\"8.108\";s:3:\"iso\";s:3:\"800\";s:13:\"shutter_speed\";s:17:\"0.033333333333333\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";}}'),(646,225,'_wp_attached_file','2014/08/Itmum-for-website-copy.jpg'),(647,225,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:5:{s:5:\"width\";i:3041;s:6:\"height\";i:2676;s:4:\"file\";s:34:\"2014/08/Itmum-for-website-copy.jpg\";s:5:\"sizes\";a:5:{s:9:\"thumbnail\";a:4:{s:4:\"file\";s:34:\"Itmum-for-website-copy-150x150.jpg\";s:5:\